<paragraph blockId="27.[168,776,1620,2091]" box="[206,244,1737,1756]" pageId="27" pageNumber="1030">351.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[168,776,1620,2091]" pageId="27" pageNumber="1030">
Hemicryptophytes, native with wide distribution in the Southern Cone Region of South America; previously recorded in 
<collectingRegion box="[300,548,1833,1857]" country="Argentina" name="Buenos Aires" pageId="27" pageNumber="1030">Buenos Aires province</collectingRegion>
but not in mountain range areas.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[168,776,1620,2091]" pageId="27" pageNumber="1030">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[206,386,1900,1924]" pageId="27" pageNumber="1030">Characteristics.</emphasis>
Perennial, rhizomatous herb with tetragonal stems. Leaves glabrous, with ovate-oblong shape, acute apex and attenuate base. Flowers: terminal or subtermianl, in groups of 1–3 flowers per peduncle; corolla and anthers white. Fruit: 2 mericarps with pubescence at the top.
</paragraph>
