<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="1030" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="27.[813,1420,562,821]" pageId="27" pageNumber="1030">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[850,980,562,586]" pageId="27" pageNumber="1030">Comments.</emphasis>
This is a very frequent species in the study area. It grows in full sunlight conditions with other short species in deep and moderately deep soils on grassland slopes and at the summit. This species has been described as an annual species (
<bibRefCitation author="Flora Argentina" box="[1173,1412,697,721]" pageId="27" pageNumber="1030" refId="ref30575" refString="Flora Argentina (2017) Plantas vasculares de la Republica Argentina. http: // www. floraargentina. edu. ar. Accessed on: 2017 - 9 - 25." type="url" year="2017">
Flora 
<collectingCountry box="[1240,1346,697,721]" name="Argentina" pageId="27" pageNumber="1030">Argentina</collectingCountry>
2017
</bibRefCitation>
) contrary to the specimens seen in the Paititi Reserve, which are hemicryptophyte herbs as previously described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Cabrera AL" box="[846,1022,797,821]" pageId="27" pageNumber="1030" refId="ref29399" refString="Cabrera AL (1965 b) Ericaceas a Caliceraceas. Flora de la Provincia de Buenos Aires. Coleccion Cientifica Instituto Nacional de Tecnologia Agropecuaria. Tomo 4 (5). Instituto Nacional de Tecnologia Agropecuaria, Buenos Aires, 434 pp." type="book" year="1965">Cabrera (1965b)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Delprete PG &amp; Smith LB &amp; Klein RM" box="[1073,1305,797,821]" pageId="27" pageNumber="1030" refId="ref30228" refString="Delprete PG, Smith LB, Klein RM (2005) Rubiaceas. In: Reis A (Ed.) Flora Ilustrada Catarinense. Herbario Barbosa Rodrigues, Itajai, 349 - 842." type="book" year="2005">Delprete et al. (2005)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
